                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #121r" facs="001 002 003 123">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso), 121r</locus> blank except for scrawls
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#1r" facs="003"> f.1r, upper right margin</locus>: Instruction for barren woman to recite <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps1"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps1</span></ref>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#12v" facs="015"> f. 12v, upper margin</locus>: <q>“When the official or the king becomes angry with you, recite Psalm 19 over oil and anoint your face.”</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a3">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#74v" facs="077">Fol. 74v</locus>: <q>“When a husband and wife disagree, recite (this psalm, 118) over butter and anoint your body.”</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a4">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, upper margin</locus>: in reference to Ps. 121 (E.T.) <q>“When you experience no blessing, recite ‘I will look’ [this psalm] over water and sprinkle your house and also recite when you travel.”</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a5">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#107v" facs="110">Fol. 107v</locus>: Note of ownership, <q>This book belongs to Mämǝre Wäldä Giyorgis</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a6">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#120r" facs="122">Fol. 120r</locus>:
                        <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6946InvocationMary">Invocation to the
                                                  Virgin Mary and Jesus Christ for protection</ref> which mentions <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2533Baselyos">Bāsǝlyos</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5226haylase">Ḫāyla Śǝllāse I</persName>, and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6642MananAs">Manan ʾAsfāw</persName>.
                      Thus, the concluding prayer was written somewhere between 1951 and 1959.
                      The prayer is written in a well-trained hand and shows the essential elements of the genre,
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                        ስብሐት፡ ለአብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ለዓለም፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም። ሰአሊ፡ ለነ፡ ቅድስት፡ ድንግል፡ ማርያም። ምሕረተ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልድኪ። የሐውጸነ፡ እምዓርያም። ሰአል፡ ለነ፡ ዳዊት። ቅድመ፡ መንበሩ፡ ለጸባዖት። ኦአምላከ፡ ዳዊት። አድኅነነ፡ እምዕለት፡ እኪት። ወባልሐነ፡ እምኲሉ፡ መንሱት። እለ፡ ወለዱነ፡ በሥጋ። ወእለ፡ ሐጸኑነ፡ በመንፈስ። ቅዱስ፡ ወእለ፡ አስተምሐሩነ፡ ቃለ፡ ሃይማኖት። ኅቡረ፡ ይምሐረነ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፡ በመንግሥተ። ሰማያት፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ (እቀቦ)፡ ለጳጳስነ፡ ባስልዮስ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ እቀቦ፡ ለንጉሥነ። ኃይለ፡ ሥላሌ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀባ፡ ለንግሥትነ፡ ወለተ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀባ፡ ለሀገሪትነ፡ ኢትዮጵያ። ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀብ፡ ሕይወቶ፡ ወሥረይ፡ ኃጢአቶ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ኦእግዚኦ፡ ዕቀባ፡ ለዓመትከ። ወለተ፡ ወልድ፡
                      </foreign>(the concluding portion is covered by the painting on f. 120v)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a7">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#121v" facs="124">Fol. 121v</locus> in pen: Note of later ownership: <q>“This bible belongs to Deacon Sǝyum.”</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#43v #55v #65r #83v" facs="046 058 067 086">folss. 43v, 55v, 65r, 83v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#16r #23v #50r #51v #63v" facs="018 026 052 054 066">16r, 23v, 50r, 51v, 63v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and in another case interlinearly where the symbol (┬) is used (<locus target="#62v" facs="065">62v, </locus>, line 19);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#60v #78r #102r #103r" facs="063 080 104 105">60v, 78r, 102r, 103r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#31r #39r #43r #90r" facs="033 041 045 092">31r, 39r, 43r, 90r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is
                          addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where
                          the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                      </item>

